<statement><div><p>The vertices of triangle <m> \triangle ABC </m> are<m> A\, ({-2}, {9}), B\,({8}, {7})\, \text{and} C\, ({5}, {4}) </m>. The triangle is enlarged with centre <m> (0,0) </m> and scale factor <m>{\frac{1}{2}}</m>. Find the coordinates of the image of <m> \triangle ABC </m>.</p>
<p>Write your answer in form of<alert> [x,y] </alert></p>
<p>A' = <fillin characters="5" name="ans1"/> </p>
<p>B' = <fillin characters="5" name="ans2"/> </p>
<p>C' = <fillin characters="5" name="ans3"/> </p>
<p/></div></statement>
<solution><div><h3>Worked solution</h3>
<p>Given the centre of enlargement is <m>(0,0)</m> and the scale factor <m>k</m>, We find the coordinates of the image as follows;
</p>
<p><m>(x' ,y') = (kx, ky)</m></p>
<p>Applying this to the given co-odinates we get;</p>
<p><m>A' = ({\frac{1}{2}} \times {-2}), ({\frac{1}{2}} \times {9}) = ({-1}, {\frac{9}{2}})</m></p>
<p><m>B' = ({\frac{1}{2}} \times {8}),( {\frac{1}{2}} \times {7}) = ({4}, {\frac{7}{2}})</m></p>
<p><m>C' = ({\frac{1}{2}} \times {5}), ({\frac{1}{2}} \times {4}) = ({\frac{5}{2}}, {2})</m></p>
<p>Verticies of the image = A' (<m>{-1}</m>, <m>{\frac{9}{2}}</m>), B' = (<m>{4}</m>, <m>{\frac{7}{2}}</m>) and  C' = (<m>{\frac{5}{2}}</m>, <m>{2}</m>).</p></div></solution>
<answer><p><m>\left[ -1 , \frac{9}{2} \right] </m></p></answer>
<answer><p><m>\left[ 4 , \frac{7}{2} \right] </m></p></answer>
<answer><p><m>\left[ \frac{5}{2} , 2 \right] </m></p></answer>
